It's a bog standard TLROM. Try this:<br /><br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Buy a <a href="http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.php?cPath=24&amp;products_id=34" class="postlink">PowerPak</a> or <a href="http://krikzz.com/index.php?route=product/product&amp;product_id=59" class="postlink">EverDrive-N8</a>. These are adapters to use camera memory cards with a Nintendo Entertainment System. I own a PowerPak, as does NovaSquirrel. </li><li>Load the ROM image and the latest mapper support package for your adapter on a blank CF or SD card. </li><li>Insert the card into the adapter and the adapter into your NES Control Deck. </li><li>Turn on the NES. </li><li>Select the game from the menu. </li></ol><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Aug 05, 2014 12:42 pm</p><hr />
